feed.title: Aladdin The Musical
feed.address: Prince Edward Theatre 28 Old Compton St, London W1D 4HS
feed.transport: Leicester Square, Tottenham Court Road Station
feed.description: The classic hit film has been brought to thrilling life on stage, featuring all the songs from the Academy Award-winning score, together with new music written for this production.
feed.shortDescription: The classic hit film has been brought to thrilling life on stage.

feed.title: Wicked at the Apollo Victoria
feed.address: Apollo Victoria Wilton Rd London SW1V 1LG
feed.description: When Dorothy famously triumphed over the Wicked Witch, we only ever heard one side of the story. Wicked tells the incredible untold story of an unlikely but profound friendship between two girls who first meet as sorcery students at Shiz University. The blonde and very popular Glinda and a misunderstood green girl named Elphaba.
feed.shortDescription: When Dorothy famously triumphed over the Wicked Witch, we only ever heard one side of the story.

feed.title: Matilda The Musical
feed.address: Cambridge Theatre Earlham Street, London, WC2H 9HU
feed.description: Matildas parents think she is a nuisance and she thinks, quite rightly, they are only interested in watching telly. Life is not much better at school, where the monstrous headmistress Miss Trunchbull terrifies both students and teachers alike. Then one day Matilda discovers she has a very special power and decides its time the grown-ups were taught a lesson. Be warned, the children are revolting!
feed.shortDescription: Matildas parents think she is a nuisance and she thinks, quite rightly, they are only interested in watching telly.

feed.title: The Lion King at the Lyceum Theatre
feed.address: The Lyceum Theatre 21 Wellington Street London WC2E 7RQ
feed.description: Set against the majesty of the Serengeti Plains to the evocative rhythms of Africa, this spectacular production explodes with glorious colours, stunning effects and enchanting music to tell the timeless story of Simba and his epic journey to fulfil his destiny as King of the Pridelands.The show is 2h 30m including one interval.
feed.shortDescription: Set against the majesty of the Serengeti Plains to the evocative rhythms of Africa.

feed.title: Mamma Mia!
feed.address: Novello Theatre Aldwych London WC2B 4LD
feed.description: Judy Craymers bold idea of turning the insanely catchy songs of ABBA into a musical has paid off splendidly, in every sense box office figures for Mamma Mia! are as eye-watering as its outfits.
feed.shortDescription: Judy Craymers bold idea of turning the insanely catchy songs of ABBA into a musical.

feed.title: Les Miserables at The Queens Theatre
feed.address: Queens Theatre Shaftesbury Avenue London W1D 6BA
feed.description: Ex-convict Jean Valjean is hunted for decades by the ruthless policeman Javert after he breaks parole. When Valjean agrees to care for factory worker Fantines young daughter, Cosette, their lives change forever.
feed.shortDescription: Ex-convict Jean Valjean is hunted for decades by the ruthless policeman Javert after he breaks parole.

feed.title: Motown The Musical
feed.address: Shaftesbury Theatre 210 Shaftesbury Avenue, London, WC2H 8DP
feed.description: Music and lyrics from the Motown catalog and book by Motown founder Berry Gordy the production features a sixteen-piece orchestra playing 50 Motown tracks including Aint No Mountain High Enough, Ill Be There, Dancing In The Street, Stop! In The Name Of Love, My Girl and I Heard It through the Grapevine. Charles Randolph Wrights production tells the story behind the classic hits.
feed.shortDescription: Music and lyrics from the Motown catalog and book by Motown.

feed.title: 42nd Street
feed.address: Catherine Street, London, WC2B 5JF
feed.description: Broadways Biggest Show, on the West Ends Biggest Stage. 42nd Street is the song and dance, American dream fable of Broadway. Young Peggy Sawyer is fresh off the bus from small town America and just another face in the chorus line on Broadways newest show. But when the leading lady gets injured, Peggy might just have the shot at stardom shes always dreamed of…
feed.shortDescription: Broadways Biggest Show, on the West Ends Biggest Stage.

feed.title: The Book of Mormon
feed.address: 31 Coventry Street, London, W1D 6AS
feed.description: The Book of Mormon is a musical comedy about two young Mormon missionaries who travel to Africa to preach the Mormon religion. First staged in 2011, the play mocks various Mormon beliefs and practices.
feed.shortDescription: The Book of Mormon is a musical comedy about two young Mormon missionaries who travel to Africa.

feed.title: Thriller Live
feed.address: 29 Shaftesbury Avenue, London, W1D 7ES
feed.description: Thriller Live is a two and a half hour concert revue celebrating the music of The Jackson 5 and the solo work and life of Michael Jackson.
feed.shortDescription: Thriller Live is a two and a half hour concert revue celebrating the music of The Jackson 5.

feed.title: Chicago
feed.address: Phoenix Theatre 110 Charing Cross Road, London, WC2H 0JP
feed.description:
The worlds longest-running American musical, the multi-award-winning CHICAGO, returns to Londons West End. Oscar winner Cuba Gooding Jr. will make his UK stage debut starring as fast-talking lawyer Billy Flynn, he will be joined by stage veterans Sarah Soetaert as Roxie Hart, Josefina Gabrielle as Velma Hart,  and Ruthie Henshall playing Mama Morton.

Roxy Hart has always wanted to be a star but cant quite seem to catch a break. Things seem poised to change when she is arrested for the murder of her lover. Roxy decided to become the medias new darling and begins vying for the spotlight, and the attention of their lawyer Billy Flynn played by Cub Gooding Jr., with her idol, nightclub performer and accused double-murderess Velma Kelly.
feed.shortDescription: The worlds longest-running American musical, the multi-award-winning CHICAGO.

feed.title: Dreamgirls
feed.address: Savoy Theatre Strand, London, WC2R 0ET
feed.description:
Dreamgirls tells the story of a trio of women from Chicago, Illinois who dream of making their mark on the music world. Dreamgirls follows the rise to fame of the Dreamettes, later The Dreams.

Curvaceous and opinionated Effie teams up with Lorrell and Deena to become the Dreams. Eventually, as the girls start to make their way in the business they have to decide how much compromise they are willing to make to hit it big. Effie is replaced by the slimmer, more commercially appealing Deena and The Dreams hit their stride.
feed.shortDescription: Dreamgirls tells the story of a trio of women from Chicago.

feed.title: School of Rock
feed.address: Gillian Lynne theatre 166 drury lane, London WC2B 5PW
feed.description: School of Rock the Musical features music by the incomparable Andrew Lloyd Webber with lyrics by Glenn Slater and a book by Julian Fellowes. Based on the hit 2003 film, this irresistible new rock musical follows Dewey Finn a wannabe rock star and guitarist who is down on his luck and decided to make a bit of quick money by posing as a supply teacher at a prestigious prep school.
feed.shortDescription: School of Rock the Musical features music by the incomparable Andrew Lloyd Webber.

feed.title: The Tina Turner
feed.address: Aldwych Theatre 49 Aldwych, London, WC2B 4DF
feed.description:
The musical will be based on the often tumultuous life and legendary music of international recording artist Tina Turner.

Tina Turner was born Anna Mae Bullock and raised in Nutbush, Tennessee. From humble beginnings, Tina would rise to fame as the Queen of Rock n Roll and go on to sell more concert tickets than any other solo artist.

feed.title: Phantom of the Opera
feed.address: Her Majestys Theatre Haymarket, London, SW1Y 4QL
feed.description:
Andrew Lloyd Webbers glittering musical is the most successful of all time with more than 100 million Phantom of the Opera tickets sold worldwide and it has won over 50 major theatre awards.

Far beneath the majesty and splendour of the Paris Opera House, hides the Phantom in a shadowy existence. Shamed by his physical appearance and feared by all, the love he holds for his beautiful student Christine is so strong that even her heart cannot resist.
feed.shortDescription: Far beneath the majesty and splendour of the Paris Opera House, hides the Phantom in a shadowy existence.

feed.title: The King and I
feed.address: London Palladium 8 Argyll Street, London, W1F 7TF
feed.description: This classic musical tale of East meets West brings us to the court of the King of Siam who is eager to change the way he is viewed by the world. Anna, a refined Welsh widow is tasked with educating the royal children in the ways of the West. What could ever develop between two people so firmly rooted in their personal, and often deeply opposed, traditions and values?
feed.shortDescription: This classic musical tale of East meets West brings us to the court of the King of Siam who is eager to change the way he is viewed by the world.

feed.title: WAITRESS
feed.address: 411-412 Strand London, WC2R 0NH
feed.description: Featuring an all female creative team, including six-time Grammy Award-nominee Sara Bareilles who provides the music and lyrics. Based on the film by Adrienne Shelley, Waitress follows expert pie-maker Jenna as she navigates the highs and lows of her small-town life.
feed.extraDescription: Waitress follows Jenna, a top notch pie maker trapped in a loveless marriage. Her prospects seem about to change when she learns of a baking contest in another county and meets the towns new doctor. But does Jenna have the courage and resilience to grasp happiness? A celebration, of true friendship, motherhood and of course pies, this show has all the right ingredients.

feed.title: THE TWILIGHT ZONE
feed.address: Ambassadors Theatre West Street London WC2H 9ND
feed.description: This ones for fans of the weird, the unexplained and the downright impossible. Its Anne Washburn’s unsettling and often surreal show based on the 1960s cult TV series of the same name.
feed.extraDescription: The cast includes returning cast members Oliver Alvin-Wilson, Adrianna Bertola and Neil Haigh. They will be joined by Alisha Bailey, Natasha J Barnes, Nicholas Karimi, Dan Crossley, Dyfan Dwyfor, Lauren O'Neill and Matthew Steer.

feed.title: HORRIBLE HISTORIES: BARMY BRITAIN PART 4
feed.address: 31 Shaftesbury Avenue London W1D 7ES
feed.transport: Piccadilly Circus, Leicester Square, Charing Cross
feed.station: Piccadilly Circus, Leicester Square, Charing Cross
feed.description: Horrible Histories Live On Stage is based upon the best selling book series by Terry Deary. Horrible Histories brings back people from history from heroes, villains, kings and queens of  the past with all the facts and lots of laughs.

feed.title: JOSEPH AND THE AMAZING TECHNICOLOR DREAMCOAT
feed.address: 8 Argyll Street Soho London W1F 7TF
feed.description: Joseph and the amazing technicolor dreamcoat, is based on the biblical tale of one Jacob's favourite son. The show follows Joseph after he receives the gift of a magnificent coat from his father. His luck takes a dip after he is sold into slavery by his dangerously jealous brothers. The story started out as a 1969 concept album before receiving its professional debut at the 1972 Edinburgh International Festival. It has gone on to enjoy soaring success; it has been translated into a movie, toured extensively, performed by amateur and school groups and even sparked a reality TV series to discover the next Joseph for the stage.
feed.extraDescription: Its soundtrack is famous the world over, including numbers such as Any Dream Will Do and Close Every Door to Me.

feed.title: HARRY POTTER AND THE CURSED CHILD
feed.address: Palace Theatre 109-113 Shaftesbury Avenue, London, W1V 8AY
feed.station: Leicester Square (3 min walk), Tottenham Court Road (6 min walk)
feed.description: JK Rowlings eighth instalment of the beloved Harry Potter series plays at the West End's Palace Theatre to sold out audiences. Conceived and written by Jack Thorne and JK Rowling, and directed by John Tiffany, the play follows Harry Potter and his family 19 years after we left them in Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows. Harry is now an employee of the Ministry of Magic, a husband and a father of three. Can his youngest son Albus carry the weight of his fathers legacy, or are there darker forces at work?
feed.extraDescription: Harry Potter and the Cursed Child features beloved characters and some incredible special effects that really bring the magic to life.  The show is presented in two separate parts which can be seen on the same day or, alternatively, on consecutive evenings.
feed.runtime: Part One, 2hrs 40mins including one interval and Part Two, 2hrs 35mins including one interval

feed.title: THE SNOWMAN
feed.address: Portugal St London  WC2A 2HT
feed.station: Charing Cross (13 min walk), Holborn, Temple
feed.description: The snowman is based on the classic Christmas book by Raymond Briggs, The Snowman sees a boy and his magical snowman embark on a winter wonderland adventure to the North Pole! Along the way, they have to escape from Jack Frost, but they get some help along the way from new friends: An Ice Princess, Father Christmas, and a group of dancing penguins.
feed.extraDescription:
The story of The Snowman is best known for the 1982 animated television special, which was nominated for an Academy Award. The silent animation featured the now-classic song ‘Walking in the Air’, which was famously covered by Aled Jones a few years later.

Walking in the Air features in this stage adaptation of The Snowman, along with other music by Howard Blake. The Snowman features a mixture of live music, storytelling, dance, and magic which will enchant and delight all the family.
feed.runtime: Running Time: 1 hour 50 minutes (including a 20 min interval)

feed.title: COME FROM AWAY
feed.address: Charing Cross Road, London, WC2H 0JG
feed.description: The new Canadian multi award-winning musical  is based on the true, remarkable events of 9 11 and delves into the heart of a community rocked by the shocking events. A thrilling, uplifting tale that sheds light on a terrifying event. As uneasiness grows and tensions tighten, friendships are forged in the dark, as this uplifting musical ultimately shows the light. As nerves run high, gratitude transforms into new relationships, music soars as culture clashes and differences of opinion are put aside.
feed.runtime: Booking until 14 September 2019 Running Time: 1 hour 40 minutes

feed.title: MARY POPPINS
feed.address: Prince Edward Theatre Old Compton Street London W1D 4HS
feed.description: The magical Mary Poppins returns to the West End in Autumn 2019, ready to delight and amaze audiences. The show features the classic songs by the Sherman Brothers from the film and stars Zizi Strallen and Charlie Stemp as Mary Poppins and Bert.
feed.extraDescription: The production originally opened back in December 2004 and enjoyed a successful three year run, accruing over 1,250 performances.  After playing London and Broadway, it was revised and went on to be staged around the world to sell-out houses.
feed.runtime: Running Time: 2 hours 40 minutes (with an interval)

feed.title: WHERE IS PETER RABBIT
feed.address: Theatre Royal Haymarket 18 Suffolk Street, London, SW1Y 4H
feed.transport: Piccadilly Circus, Charing Cross, Leicester Square
feed.station: Piccadilly Circus, Charing Cross, Leicester Square
feed.description: Enter the magical world of Beatrix Potter in this enchanting theatrical spectacular. Watch your favourite stories and beloved characters from Beatrix Potters tales come to life! Meet Jemima Puddle-Duck, do the laundry with Mrs Tiggy-Winkle, watch out for the wicked Mr McGregor, and fall in love with cheeky Peter Rabbit. The show is filled with beautiful handcrafted puppets, 14 original songs, and a dusting of magic.
feed.extraDescription: Where is Peter Rabbit? Includes voiceovers from national treasure Miriam Margolyes and TV and stage personality Griff Rhys Jones. The songs, written by Sir Alan Ayckbourn, will all be sung live on top of a delightful dancing set.

feed.title: ONLY FOOLS AND HORSES THE MUSICAL
feed.address: Theatre Royal Haymarket 18 Suffolk Street, London, SW1Y 4H
feed.transport: Piccadilly Circus, Charing Cross, Leicester Square
feed.station: Piccadilly Circus, Charing Cross, Leicester Square
feed.description: Join Del Boy, Rodney and The Gang In An All New Musical, Based on the record breaking, beloved television series. All the familiar elements are here, from the London street markets and cockney accents to the dodgy deals and hilarious scrapes. Rewind to Peckham in 1989 and find out what Del Boy, Rodney and Grandad are up to.
feed.extraDescription: Only Fools and Horses is a British sitcom created and written by John Sullivan. It follows Derek Del Boy Trotter is a fast talking market trader living in South London with his younger brother, Rodney. In order to try to get rich, the brothers dabble in black market trading through an unregistered company they own, Trotters Independent Trading Co. But many of their deals end up backfiring on them.

feed.title: Miss Saigon at the Prince Edward
feed.address: Prince Edward Theatre 28 Old Compton St W1D 4HS
feed.transport: Piccadilly Circus or Leicester Square Station
feed.description: This epic musical love story tells the tragic tale of young bar girl Kim, orphaned by war, who falls in love with an American GI called Chris â but their lives are torn apart by the fall of Saigon.

feed.title: Cats the Musical at the London
feed.address: London Palladium 8 Argyll Street London W1F 7TF
feed.description: On just one special night of the year, all Jellicle cats meet at the Jellicle Ball where Old Deuteronomy, their wise and benevolent leader, makes the Jellicle choice and announces which of them will go up to The Heaviside Layer and be reborn into a whole new Jellicle life.
